2star  aLanguage Contact. An International Handbook offers a comprehensive overview of current topics in research on language contact. Broadly conceived, it stands out for its international approach to language contact, complementing the theoretical state-of-the-art with examples from traditionally eclipsed areas and languages. Next to a thorough introductory overview of the ground-breaking methodological and theoretical approaches that shaped the discipline, ample attention goes to the new and innovative insights on language contact in the 21st century. Combining concise introductory contributions with in-depth treatment of the most relevant case studies in the field, the handbook speaks to both junior and established scholars.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Contact, Bilingualism.1 aAbdollahi, Fatemeh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAbtahian, Maya Ravindranath, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdamou, Evangelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdams, Katharine Donnelly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBekker, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirchfield, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBourgeois, Laura French, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradley, Andrew F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrenzinger, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCichocki, Wladyslaw, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCárdenas, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo